    • Method Detail

      • getID

        int getID()
        Get token ID. The token ID is compiler-specific value. Each token must have unique ID.
        Returns:
        ID of the token

      • getType

        int getType()
        Get token type. The token type mus be one of the pre-defined constants located inside this interface (e.g. RESERVED, PREPROCESSOR, etc.).
        Returns:
        type of the token

      • getLine

        int getLine()
        Get 0-based starting line (row) of token position.
        Returns:
        start line number of the token

      • getColumn

        int getColumn()
        Get 0-based starting column of token position.
        Returns:
        start column number of the token

      • getOffset

        int getOffset()
        Get 0-based starting offset of token position.
        Returns:
        starting offset of the token in the source code

      • getLength

        int getLength()
        Get length of the token.
        Returns:
        length of the token

      • getErrorString

        String getErrorString()
        Get error string for this token. If the token is not errorneous, return empty string ("").
        Returns:
        error string message for this token

      • getText

        String getText()
        Get token value.
        Returns:
        token value

      • isInitialLexicalState

        boolean isInitialLexicalState()
        Check if the token is in initial lexical state. Initial lexical state represents a position in the source code, from what the lexical analyzer can safely start parsing the source code - as it would parse it from the start of the document. They are useful especially for syntax highlighting.
        Returns:
        true if token is in initial lexical state; false otherwise.
